Hi there,

One way to do this is to included a continuous running item in the 
sentences to make them all the same number of items long, then 
group by this number so it will sort them but not mess up the 
order of each individual sentence....

> ! First sentence
> +1 <umb +Space><mpr +Space> "I" * <cr>;
> +2 <umb +Space><mpr +Space> "think." * <cr>;
 include here-   250 c;  - then group by 3 on the first line...

> 
> ! Second sentence
> +3 <umb +Space><mpr +Space> "Therefore" * <cr>;
> +4 <umb +Space><mpr +Space> "I" * <cr>;
> +5 <umb +Space><mpr +Space> "am." * <cr>;

